ART EVENT FILES

These are standard art/ROOT event files. The repo-specific content is the set
of products written into each event.

`%ifb_%tc_imageprod.root`
`-- imageprod:NuSlice -> std::vector<image::ImageProduct>`
    `-- usually 3 entries, one per plane: U, V, W

`image::ImageProduct` fields
- `view` (`int`): plane id.
- `width`, `height` (`uint32_t`): image dimensions.
- `hit_count` (`uint32_t`): number of hits contributing to the plane image.
- `origin_x`, `origin_y` (`float`): lower-left image origin in projected world coordinates.
- `pixel_w`, `pixel_h` (`float`): pixel size in world units.
- `vertex_row`, `vertex_col` (`int32_t`): reconstructed neutrino-vertex pixel, or `-1`.
- `index` (`vector<uint32_t>`): flattened pixel indices.
- `adc` (`vector<float>`): ADC values aligned with `index`.
- `semantic` (`vector<uint8_t>`): semantic class labels aligned with `index`.
- `in_nu_slice` (`vector<uint8_t>`): 1 if the pixel receives neutrino-slice contribution.

Sparse image rule
- `index[k]`, `adc[k]`, `semantic[k]`, and `in_nu_slice[k]` refer to the same active pixel.
- Only active pixels are stored.

`%ifb_%tc_inference.root`
|-- imageprod:NuSlice -> `std::vector<image::ImageProduct>`
|-- inferenceprod -> `image::InferencePredProduct`
`-- inferenceprod -> `image::InferencePerfProduct`

`image::InferencePredProduct`
`-- per_model[]`
    |-- `model` (`string`)
    `-- `scores` (`vector<float>`)

`image::InferencePerfProduct`
`-- per_model[]`
    |-- `model` (`string`)
    |-- `t_write_req_ms`
    |-- `t_exec_total_ms`
    |-- `t_read_resp_ms`
    |-- `t_child_total_ms`
    |-- `t_child_setup_ms`
    |-- `t_child_infer_ms`
    |-- `t_child_post_ms`
    `-- `child_max_rss_mb`

`%ifb_%tc_fullchain_nuselection.root`
|-- same custom event products as `%ifb_%tc_inference.root`
`-- event filtering is applied by `EventSelectionFilter`

Important note
- `EventSelectionFilter` writes TTrees into the histogram ROOT file, not a new
  custom event product into the art event file.

`%ifb_extragenie1_rhc.root`
- Output file exists, but the internal payload is defined mainly by the
  upstream included event-weight configuration, not by local product classes in
  this repository.

