Event-weight encoding
- The `weightsFlux`, `weightsGenie`, `weightsReint`, `weightsPPFX`,
  `weightsGenieUp`, and `weightsGenieDn` vectors are compressed
  `unsigned short` representations produced in code by scaling the original
  floating weights by about `1000`.
- Checked-in production selection config uses `genieAllUniverses: 500`.
- `dev/image_dev.fcl` overrides this to `100`.
- NuMI tuple mode also enables `weightsPPFX` with 600 universes.

