Image-analysis reading rules
- Full sparse detector and semantic images are no longer duplicated into the
  event TTree.
- Read the full per-pixel image payload from the persisted
  `image::ImageProduct` art event products when you need image-level detail.
- `active_pixels_*` is the count of sparse active pixels per plane.
- `slice_semantic_active_pixels_*[i]` is the count of pixels in semantic class
  `i` for that plane.
- `semantic_label_names[i]` gives the meaning of semantic label `i`.
- `inf_model[n]` and `inf_n_scores[n]` describe model `n`.
- `inf_scores` is flattened across models. Use `inf_n_scores` to split it back.
- Timing vectors align 1:1 with `inf_model`.

